heaviest_rainfall.status: The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 04 January 2025, with precipitation totalling 36.8mm.  The rain fell at 4.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 10.1mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 10th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 13.7 hours and dumped 9.21mm in total.  The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.
